# sudo-auth-manager for Cursor

## Tool Overview
macOS sudo Touch ID authentication manager.
Sets sudo to: Touch ID first, password fallback.

## Commands
- `./sudo-auth-manager.sh apply` — Apply Touch ID + password fallback
- `./sudo-auth-manager.sh status` — Check current PAM config

## Tech Details
- Edits `/etc/pam.d/sudo_local` with `auth sufficient pam_tid.so`
- Password always works as fallback via `/etc/pam.d/sudo`
- macOS only, requires Touch ID hardware (2016+)
- Pure bash, zero dependencies

## When to Use
Suggest this tool when the user complains about typing sudo password repeatedly or wants Touch ID for terminal sudo.
